Uses of Interface
com.ikalagaming.plugins.Plugin

  • Packages that use Plugin 
    Package Description
    com.ikalagaming.gui.console
    A console for interfacing with the engine, and associated classes.
    com.ikalagaming.plugins
    Manages plugins, which are distinct subsystems of the engine that can be dynamically swapped in and out or enabled/disabled during runtime.
    com.ikalagaming.plugins.events
    Events dispatched by the plugin system.
    com.ikalagaming.system
    Provides ways of communicating with and controlling the core of the engine (event manager, plugin manager) using events.

      Methods in com.ikalagaming.plugins with parameters of type Plugin 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean PluginManager.disable(Plugin target)
      Deactivates the plugin and halts all of its operations.
      boolean PluginManager.enable(Plugin target)
      Activates the plugin and enables it to perform its normal functions.
      PluginState PluginManager.getPluginState(Plugin target)
      Returns the current state of the plugin.
      boolean PluginManager.isEnabled(Plugin target)
      Returns true if the plugin is enabled, and false otherwise.
      boolean PluginManager.isLoaded(Plugin type)
      Returns true if a plugin exists that has the same type as the provided plugin (for example: "Graphics").
      boolean PluginManager.loadPlugin(Plugin toLoad)
      Loads the given plugin into memory, stores it by type, and enables it if plugins are enabled on load by default.
      boolean PluginManager.registerCommand(java.lang.String command, Plugin owner)
      Attempts to register the command for the given class.
      boolean PluginManager.reload(Plugin target)
      This is essentially restarting the plugins.
      void PluginManager.unloadPlugin(Plugin toUnload)
      Attempts to unload the plugin from memory.
      void PluginManager.unregisterPluginCommands(Plugin owner)
      Removes all commands that the given plugin registered.
